
[1]antimetabole

   ANTIMETAB'OLE, n. antimetab'oly. [Gr. against, and mutation.]

   In rhetoric, a setting of two things in opposition to each other; as,
   an honorable action may be attended with labor, but the labor is soon
   past, and the honor is immortal.
